Active in the second half of the 20th century: Born in or after 1950 and died in or before 2000;
Textual complexity: Average lexical diversity score of their works;
High linguistic variety: Higher average lexical diversity scores;
Worked on more than a single work: Authors with more than one literary work.

sql:
SELECT project_name, start_date
FROM collaborative_projects
WHERE start_date > '2000-01-01';

external_knowledge:
- "sowers of new seeds" refers to authors;
- "garden of modern literature" represents the literary works published after the year 2000;
- "linguistic soil" corresponds to the lexical diversity of the works;
- "since the dawn of the 21st century" indicates after the year 2000.

sql:
SELECT lw.title, a.annotation_text
FROM literary_works lw
LEFT JOIN annotations a ON lw.work_id = a.work_id;

external_knowledge:
The 'dawn of the new millennium' refers to the year 2000 and onwards;
The 'linguistic richness' refers to the lexical diversity scores of the literary works;
The 'total word counts' and 'uniqueness of their vocabulary' refer to the work's word counts and unique word counts, respectively.
